		<hr size="1">I still don't understand why Verant won't allow the use of the Bow as a viable alternative.  Are they afraid that we, the melee classes of Norrath, (we being warriors and rangers) will take away the GOD GIVEN right of the NECROS and DRUIDS, and MAGES to solo?  Woooooo....I'm shaking in my boots.  My usual damage is in they mid 20's usualy with an occasional trip into the 30's.  My highest Crit yet is 62.  I don't mind the delay on the bow so much, as I mind doing CRAP damage.  It seems to me that they base the damage of the bow strictly on the bow damage and add the arrow damage, X2 for crits.  THIS, pisses me off.  I can understand maybe not adding our str to the damage as you aren't using your str to propell the arrow.  But they should allow us to add our SKILL LEVEL and PLAYER level and up the cap like melee weapons.  That wouldn't give us all the advantages of melee, but it sure as hell would help.  What do you all think about that?  A good archer, in one shot, can fell just about any creature.  Being on Norrath, that has to change some what to fit the parameters, but it still needs to be better that what it currently is.  AT the very least, they need to give us back the ability to shoot right after we cast.  Its is beyond stupid to keep that from us.  We can melee RIGHT after we cast, so why can't we shoot?  VERANT EXPLAIN THAT!  I dare ya!  I don't want another stupid excuse of, oh, thats a balance thing.  THAT IS CRAP!  Ok, now before I go and get really mad, I will leave, and cool off.  Not that they read this board anyway.  Peace out.</P><P>/cheer  39 and SoW at last!</P><P>Lanandrin Mandragoran<BR>39th Season, Solusek Ro<BR>The Blood Sworn</P><P>"Our deeds in life, echo through eternity"<br>&nbsp;<br>&nbsp;<br></font>
