		<hr size="1">In respect to the original post:</P><P>Non-critcal Hit:<BR>Max damage = Bow damage + Arrow damage.</P><P>Critcal Hit:<BR>Damage = 2*(Bow damage + Arrow damage + 1)</P><P>In respect to other comments:</P><P>Yeah as an 18th Ranger, it pains me to know that sooner or later I'll have to hang my Trueshot Longbow up on its hook, and forget about it.<BR>The delay after casting is pretty bad, but its compounded by the fact that firing the bow immediately after a spell, greys out the ranged weapon button AND loses you an arrow into the bargain, WITHOUT the mob receiving a shot.<BR>But mainly its the fact that I know the damage done by my melee weapons will increase with my skill level, while this will never happen to my archery damage. Sooner or later even this Trueshot, this bow of bows, that I spent seemlying forever to create will be little more than a novelty toy, of no use other than to pull mobs.</P><P>Considering that the bow its supposed to be the Ranger's first and primary weapon, this state of affairs is pretty grim to say the least.</P><P>Faeyd 18th Ranger.</P><P>"Not all that glitters is gold. Not all who wander are lost."<br>&nbsp;<br>&nbsp;<br></font>
