		<img src="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/edit.gif" border="0" alt="Edit/Delete Message" width="18" height="13"></a>
		
		</font>
		<hr size="1">That formula is indeed incorrect. This is how it really works:</P><P>Weapons carried in the main hand are given a damage bonus (there's nothing called ambidextrous in Norrath), with the following formula:<BR>(level - 25) / 3  --&gt; 1H weapons<BR>(level - 25) / 2  --&gt; 2H weapons<BR>NB: it is unknown whether this still applies after level 50.</P><P>The maximum damageis calculated using the following formula:<BR>([Str + Skill] / 100) * Weapon Damage</P><P>So to figure out your max damage, you need to work out the second formula, and add the first to the result of the second. Hope that helps.<br>&nbsp;<br>&nbsp;<br></font>
	</font>
	</td>
</tr>
